span.span: Check the calendar to see what activities are coming up this week!

p.span: To find out the latest news from around the district, check out the latest edition of the Tiger Tribune.

span.span: It is the intent of the School District of Tigerton that the information on its website be accessible to individuals with disabilities in compliance with the requirements of Section 504 of the Rehabilitation Act of 1973 and its implementing regulations at 34 C.F.R. Part 104, and Title II of the Americans with Disabilities Act of 1990 and its implementing regulations at 28 C.F.R. Part 35.
If you have difficulty accessing information on the District’s website due to a disability, please contact us at

and provide the URL (web address) of the material you tried to access, the problem you experienced and your contact information, including your name, email address and phone number, so that we can contact you and accommodate your needs.
Attitude is Everything. Pick a Good One!

p.span: The Tigerton School District is accepting bids for
. Bids must be submitted by 4 pm on May 5, 2020.

span.span: -Due to current and constantly changing public health concerns, all in-person classes at Tigerton Elementary and High Schools are cancelled until further notice. We are currently working on alternative methods of delivering instruction to our students as needed.
For More Information about the Coronavirus Check the following sites.

span.a: Shawano County Department of Public Health

span.span: With the Cold and Flu Season in Full Swing. It's Time To Check Out Our
for Advice on Staying Healthy and Happy.
You Can Now Conveniently Make an Online Payment For Food Service by Clicking on
Under the Students & Parents Menu. Eventually, This Will Expand to Include Payments for Daycare, Fitness Center, and Other School Fees.
Our District website is, as always, under construction. We appreciate your patience as we continue to make changes and updates to our site.

The School District of Tigerton does not discriminate against pupils on the basis of sex, race, national origin, ancestry, creed, pregnancy, marital or parental status, sexual orientation, or physical, mental, emotional, or learning disability or handicap in its education programs or activities, political affiliation, arrest or conviction record, membership in the National Guard, State Defense or Reserve Component of the Military Forces of the United States or State of Wisconsin. Federal law prohibits discrimination in employment on the basis of age, race, color, national origin, sex, religion or handicap.
